data.enText: a special chair used by a king or queen to sit on at ceremonies
the position of being a king or queen

data.chText: 伊丽莎白女王于1952年即位 / 登基。
data.enText: Queen Elizabeth came/succeeded to the throne in 1952.
when Henry VIII was on the throne (= was king)
the person who really controls an organization, a country, etc. in contrast to the person who is legally in charge

tr: the position and power of an exalted person (a sovereign or bishop) who is entitled to sit in a chair of state on ceremonial occasions
the chair of state for a monarch, bishop, etc.
example: the king sat on his throne

tr: a plumbing fixture for defecation and urination
put a monarch on the throne
example: The Queen was enthroned more than 50 years ago

tr: sit on the throne as a ruler

value.def: A throne is a decorative chair used by a king, queen, or emperor on important official occasions.
You can talk about the throne as a way of referring to the position of being king, queen, or emperor.

example.tran: 女王登基 50 周年纪念日
